Package com.vijfhart.casus.tree

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LevelComparable<T>
    Objects of classes implementing this interface can be compared by level.
    Node<T extends Node<T>>
    A Node is an element in a Tree, with an optional parent node.
    Tree<T extends Node<T>>
    A Tree-structured collection containing Node elements.
    TreeIterable<T extends Node<T>>
    Sub-interface of Iterable, to indicate that a class implementing this interface can loop through a Tree.
    TreeIterator<T extends Node<T>>
    An interface to iterate over Nodes in a Tree.

    A Wrapper class to create a Tree-node out of any Comparable object.
